        "title": "fix(build): avoid stale agent-core dts warnings",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Move built-in harness message roles into the canonical agent-core message type surface so generated declarations no longer rely on relative module augmentation.\n- Keep `src/agents/sessions/messages.ts` as a runtime re-export instead of declaring OpenClaw-only augmentations against agent-core internals.\n- Add a shared tsdown package output-root helper and use it from both `tsdown.config.ts` and `scripts/tsdown-build.mjs`, so stale package declaration chunks are cleaned for every tsdown package without deleting unrelated package artifacts.\n- Add coverage that package output roots are cleaned while unrelated package `dist` folders are preserved.\n\n## Validation\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check packages/agent-core/src/types.ts packages/agent-core/src/harness/messages.ts src/agents/sessions/messages.ts scripts/lib/tsdown-output-roots.d.mts scripts/lib/tsdown-output-roots.mjs scripts/tsdown-build.mjs test/scripts/tsdown-build.test.ts tsdown.config.ts packages/agent-core/src/harness/session/session.ts packages/agent-core/src/harness/compaction/branch-summarization.ts packages/agent-core/src/harness/compaction/compaction.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/tsdown-build.test.ts packages/agent-core/src/harness/messages.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions`\n- `git diff --check`\n- Autoreview: `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main` reported no accepted/actionable findings.\n- Crabbox/Testbox: `tbx_01ksx1xgcv47npa7tgyagb5x7n`, Actions run https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/actions/runs/26691436092, command exited 0.\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: OpenClaw package builds should not leave stale tsdown declaration chunks behind, and generated agent-core declarations should not contain the relative augmentation warning that this PR set out to remove.\n\nReal environment tested: Blacksmith Testbox launched through the OpenClaw Crabbox wrapper on PR head `b9093a0a281334e7031c54291c5d56fcac23a0ad`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: From this branch, I ran a Crabbox/Testbox session with `node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider blacksmith-testbox --blacksmith-org openclaw --blacksmith-workflow .github/workflows/ci-check-testbox.yml --blacksmith-job check --blacksmith-ref main --idle-timeout 90m --ttl 240m --timing-json --shell -- \"set -euo pipefail; corepack pnpm check:changed; corepack pnpm build\"`.\n\nEvidence after fix: Copied live console output from the Crabbox/Testbox session:\n\n```text\nprovider: blacksmith-testbox\nleaseId: tbx_01ksx1xgcv47npa7tgyagb5x7n\nslug: blue-crayfish\ncommand: corepack pnpm check:changed; corepack pnpm build\nresult: {\"provider\":\"blacksmith-testbox\",\"leaseId\":\"tbx_01ksx1xgcv47npa7tgyagb5x7n\",\"slug\":\"blue-crayfish\",\"commandMs\":302006,\"totalMs\":307740,\"exitCode\":0}\nCI artifact run: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/actions/runs/26691436092\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: Testbox completed the changed checks and full build with exit code 0. The `tsdown` build completed without the earlier relative `declare module \"../types.js\"` or `declare module \"../runtime/index.js\"` generated-dts warnings, and the new tsdown clean test verifies only known tsdown package output roots are removed.\n\nWhat was not tested: No manual app UI flow; this change is build/declaration cleanup and package output-root behavior.\n",
